A 26-YEAR-OLD man sustained critical injuries after the light motor vehicle he was driving collided with a bus on the R546 on Thursday, 2 February, in Secunda, Mpumalanga. ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring said they arrived on the scene at 5.25pm with the SAPS and other paramedics. REGISTER TO COMMENT! “The man was found entrapped in his severely crumpled vehicle, still under the front end of the bus. Advanced life support interventions were initiated while fire departments started to extract him with the jaws of life,” Meiring said in a statement. He added that the man was transported to hospital, along with five adults travelling on the bus who suffered minor injuries. Meiring further said cops were still investigating.